ccn/sn83045081/1904-03-23/ed-1/seq-3/#date1=1789&index=0&rows=20&words=A+C+Marklein&searchType=basic&sequence=0&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=A.+C.+Marklein&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1</ref> <ref>https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85052076/1904-03-03/ed-1/seq-1/#date1=1789&index=0&rows=20&words=attacked+killed+lion+mountain&searchType=basic&sequence=0&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=killed+mountain+lion+attack&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1</ref><ref>https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85052020/1904-03-04/ed-1/seq-4/#date1=1789&index=2&rows=20&words=attacked+killed+lion+mountain&searchType=basic&sequence=0&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=killed+mountain+lion+attack&y=0&x=0&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=1</ref> |- |Child Brown, 2 or 14, male || January 31, 1909 || Killed by a cougar near [[Balboa, California]]. The boy was attacked while in a tent. News stories variously reported his age as 2 and 14<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=ykIwAAAAIBAJ&sjid=RUgDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4474,1187899&dq=killed%20by%20mountain%20lion&hl=en|title=The Deseret News - Google News Archive Search|publisher=|accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.coloradohistoricnewspapers.org/cgi-bin/colorado?a=d&d=TAD19090202.2.18&srpos=13&e=-------en-20--1--txt-txIN-killed%20by%20mountain%20lion-------0-#|title=Aspen Democrat February 2, 1909 — Colorado Historic Newspapers Collection|publisher=|accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref> |- | Isola Kennedy, 38, female; Earl Wilson, 10, male || July 5, 1909 || Rabid cougar attacked a woman and child in [[Morgan Hill, California|Morgan Hill]] in [[Santa Clara County, California]]. Both victims died from [[rabies]], not from the physical injuries. This is the only instance of a double fatality and the only instance where the victims succumbed to disease rather than the injuries sustained in the attack.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cheek|first1=Martin|title=Local Heroine Isola Kennedy Sacrificed Life|url=http://ww