{{Infobox comic book title| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> |title=The Thing! |image=Thing,The,Ditko1stcover.jpg |caption=''The Thing'' #12 (Feb. 1954), featuring the first comic-book cover art by [[Steve Ditko]] |schedule=Bimonthly |horror = y |genre = [[Horror comics|Horror]] |format=Anthology |publisher=[[Charlton Comics]] |startmo = Feb. |startyr = 1952 |endmo = Nov. |endyr = 1954 |issues=17 |main_char_team= |writers= |artists=[[Steve Ditko]] |pencillers= |inkers= |letterers= |colorists= |creative_team_month= |creative_team_year= |creators= |TPB = Steve Ditko's The Thing! |ISBN = 1-56685-028-2 }} '''''The Thing!''''' is an American [[horror comics|horror]] [[comic book]] published by [[Charlton Comics]] that ran 17 issues from 1952 to 1954. Its tagline was "Weird tales of suspense and horror!" After the 17th issue, it was cancelled and the series' numbering continued as ''[[Blue Beetle]]'' vol. 2.<ref name=gcd>{{gcdb series|id=14114|title=The Thing!}}</ref>
Artist [[Steve Ditko]] provided the covers for #12-15 and 17. He also illustrated stories in issues #12-15. The cover of #12 marks this industry notable's first comic-book cover art.<ref>[http://www.comics.org/credit/name/steve%20ditko/sort/chrono/ Steve Ditko] at the Grand Comics Database</ref>
In 2006, [[Pure Imagination (comics)|Pure Imagination]] released the [[Trade paperback (comics)|trade paperback]] ''Steve Ditko's The Thing!'' that reprinted all of Ditko's stories from this title, and used the cover of #15 for its cover. The back cover shows the covers from ''The Thing!'' #12, 13 and 14 and ''[[Strange Suspense Stories]]'' #22. It also included Ditko stories from Charlton's ''Mysteries of Unexplored Worlds'' #5 and #11, ''Do You Believe In Nightmares'' #1, ''Strange Suspense Stories'' #36, and ''Unusual Tales'' #25.
In 2014, the UK publisher PS Artbooks reprinted the entire series in a two-volume hardcover edition.<ref>[http://captaincomics.ning.com/profiles/blogs/ps-artbooks-presents-the-thing-vols-1-2 Captain Comics] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304201559/http://captaincomics.ning.com/profiles/blogs/ps-artbooks-presents-the-thing-vols-1-2 |date=2014-03-04 }}</ref>
